'''Passing'''
* '''Passing Yards''': 4,614 [[Neil Lomax]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1984}})
* '''Passing Touchdowns''': 30 [[Kurt Warner]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2008}})
* '''Passes Completed''': 401 [[Kurt Warner]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2008}})
* '''Passes Attempted''': 598 [[Kurt Warner]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2008}})
* '''Longest Completed Pass Thrown''': 98 Yards [[Doug Russell (American football)|Doug Russell]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1932}}) / [[Ogden Compton]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1957}}) / [[Jim Hart (American football)|Jim Hart]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1972}})
* '''Consecutive Games With a Touchdown Pass''': 22 [[Kurt Warner]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2007}}&amp;ndash;{{Cardinals NFL season|2008}})

'''Rushing'''
* '''Rushing Yards''': 1,605 [[Ottis Anderson]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1979}})
* '''Rushing Attempts''': 337 [[Edgerrin James]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2006}})
* '''Rushing Touchdowns''': 14 [[John David Crow]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1962}})
* '''Rushing Touchdowns (Rookie)''': 10 [[Tim Hightower]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2008}})
* '''Longest Rushing Attempt''': 83 yards [[John David Crow]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1958}})
* '''Rushing Yards Per Game''': 100.3 yards [[Ottis Anderson]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1979}})

'''Receiving'''
* '''Receptions''': 103 [[Larry Fitzgerald]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2005}})
* '''Receiving Yards''': 1,598 [[David Boston]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|2001}})
* '''Receiving Touchdowns''': 15 [[Sonny Randle]] ({{Cardinals NFL season|1960}})

