'''Ani DiFranco''' ({{IPAc-en|icon|ˈ|ɑː|n|iː}}; born '''Angela Maria DiFranco''' on September 23, 1970) is an American [[Grammy Award]]-winning&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.righteousbabe.com/ani/evolve/grammy.asp Evolve Wins the 2004 Grammy Award for Best Recording Package]&lt;/ref&gt; [[singer]], [[guitarist]], [[poet]], and [[songwriter]]. She has released more than 20 albums,&lt;ref name=&quot;MilwaukeeJS2006&quot;&gt;{{cite web
 | title = DiFranco makes time for radical sabbatical: Indie rocker records new album and prepares for motherhood
 | author = Gene Stout
 | publisher = The [[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]]
 | date = August 21, 2006
 | url = http://www.jsonline.com/story/index.aspx?id=486202
 | accessdate = 2008-01-02
 }} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}}&lt;/ref&gt; and is a [[feminist]] icon.&lt;ref name=&quot;DailyTexan2002&quot;&gt;
{{cite web
 | title = Sound Bites
 | author =
 | publisher = [[Daily Texan]]
 | date = September 17, 2002
 | accessdate = 2008-01-02
 | url = http://media.www.dailytexanonline.com/media/storage/paper410/news/2002/09/17/Entertainment/Sound.Bites-499123.shtml
 }}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=&quot;Salon&quot;&gt;
{{cite web
 | title = Mother Who Think: Hey hey, ho ho, the matriarchy's got to go
 | author = Lori Leibovich
 | publisher = [[Salon.com|Salon]]
 | date = March 27, 1998
 | accessdate = 2008-01-02
 | url = http://www.salon.com/mwt/feature/1998/03/27feature.html
 }}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=&quot;Newsbank&quot;&gt;
